Transport minister Fikile Mbalula says the controversial Administrative Adjudication of Road Traffic Offences Bill has been signed into law. It's a demerit system that will fundamentally change driving in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says the controversial Administrative Adjudication of Road Traffic Offences Bill has been signed into law. It's a demerit system that will fundamentally change driving in South Africa. READ: Outa to challenge AARTO demerit system Mbalula said drivers who refused to obey will face the full might of the law. He added that they will also be impounding unroadworthy vehicles.